Stats SA released South Africa’s GDP figures for the first quarter of 2019 revealing that the country’s basket of goods declined 3.2 per cent since 2018 Q4. Mining and manufacturing data which slowed this year has been linked to the country’s slow economic growth. Joining CNBC Africa to discuss South Africa’s GDP results is Bianca Botes, Corporate Treasury Manager at Peregrine Treasury Solutions and Maarten Ackerman, Chief Economist, Citadel....